HEADWORD: Unwemmed
<hw>Un*wemmed"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Not blemished;
undefiled; pure.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyclif.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With body clean and with <qex>unwemmed</qex> thought.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unwhole</ent>⟦br⟧
